without incrementing any counter. True completion count for this window is unknown but non-zero.\n- **HIGH — 2 queued tasks at full stall:** `high-1772910533.md` and `high-1772913748.md` show queue_depth=2 at 15:01. No retry triggered, no escalation fired, no stall-detector intervention visible in delegation log.\n\n### Behavioral / Protocol Compliance\n\n- **HIGH — Zero self-escalation on session mismatch:** Temujin's rules require: `WHEN tock_model != claude-opus-4-6 THEN create self-task to verify/fix model config`. This rule was written in the 12:17 reflection. No self-task was created. The rule was generated but not wired to an execution trigger.\n- **MEDIUM — No retry signal for 2 stalled high-priority tasks:** High-priority tasks with zero progress for >30 min should auto-trigger retry or escalation. Neither happened. Stall-detector dispatched to jochi (not temujin) in the 14:31 delegation log — stall-detector is not detecting temujin's stuck queue as actionable.\n\n### Telemetry Integrity\n\n- **HIGH — session_match: false is structurally undetected:** Tock reports `session_match: false` for temujin (and mongke, chagatai, jochi, ogedei). No alert fires on this condition. No pipeline step reads `session_match` and triggers remediation. This field is logged but not acted upon.\n- **MEDIUM — llm_assessment model is `lukey03/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision`:** The tock LLM assessment itself runs on the wrong model. Its recommendations are correct by accident, not by analysis quality. Tock assessment is unreliable when the assessment model is not claude-opus-4-6.\n\n### Gateway Context\n\n- **MEDIUM — 164 errors / 16.7% gateway uptime:** Infrastructure-level errors, not temujin-specific. Reduce dispatch reliability — new tasks may fail to reach temujin even after session is fixed.\n\n---\n\n## Cross-Cutting Concerns\n\n1. **Session model mismatch is fleet-wide** — mongke (glm-5), chagatai (qwen3.5-plus), jochi (kimi-k2.5), ogedei (qwen3-coder-next) all show `session_match: false`. Fixing settings.json does not fix running sessions. This pattern will repeat on every fix cycle until sessions are explicitly killed post-config-change.\n\n2. **Rename race condition affects all agents** — The 14:31 tock showed kublai=23, mongke=5, temujin=21 queue depth. At 15:01: kublai=0, mongke=0, temujin=2. Combined 47-task queue drop with 0 recorded completions across the fleet. Race condition is not temujin-specific; it inflates all queue metrics and hides all completion metrics.\n\n3. **WHEN/THEN rules not wired to execution triggers** — Four consecutive reflections have generated new rules that are never executed. Rules exist in memory files and reflection docs but nothing reads them and creates the triggering conditions.\n\n---\n\n## Prioritized Improvement List\n\n| Priority | Domain | Issue | Action |\n|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n| Critical | Execution | Active session on wrong model; settings.json fix inert until session killed | Kill temujin session process; task-watcher spawns new session with clean settings.json |\n| Critical | Telemetry | `session_match: false` fires no alert and triggers no remediation | Add `session_match: false` as alert condition in stall-detector |\n| High | Telemetry | Rename race condition hides all completed tasks | Add file lock + pre-check for `.completed.done.md` before second rename in `mark_task_completed()` |\n| High | Protocol | 2 stalled high-priority tasks with no retry/escalation | Manually retry `high-1772910533` and `high-1772913748` after session is fixed |\n| High | Protocol | WHEN/THEN rules never execute | Write rule-executor hook in reflection pipeline that converts active rules into task files |\n| Medium | Telemetry | tock LLM assessment runs on wrong model | Add model guard to tock-gather: skip LLM assessment if model != claude-opus-4-6 |\n\n---\n\n## Brainstorming: Top 3 Proposals\n\n### Proposal 1: Session Kill Hook on Config Change (CRITICAL)\n\n**Problem:** Fixing settings.json has zero effect on the running session.\n**Solution:** `post_config_change_hook.sh` — detects PID of running claude-agent for the agent, sends SIGTERM, waits for task-watcher to respawn with clean config.\n**Metric:** Time-to-correct-model drops from \"until next task-watcher restart\" to \"< 30 seconds.\"\n\n### Proposal 2: session_match Alert in Stall Detector\n\n**Problem:** `session_match: false` is logged in tock but no pipeline reads it.\n**Solution:** Add to `scripts/stall_detector.py`: if `session_match == false AND queue_depth > 0`, emit HIGH alert and create kublai task `\"Agent {name} session on wrong model — kill session\"`.\n**Metric:** Model drift incidents auto-detected within one tock cycle (30 min) instead of requiring hourly reflection.\n\n### Proposal 3: Rule Executor in Reflection Pipeline\n\n**Problem:** WHEN/THEN rules are written to memory but never executed.\n**Solution:** `rule_executor.py` step at end of each reflection — parse MEMORY.md for rules with `WHEN` conditions matching current tock state, generate concrete task files for matching rules.\n**Metric:** Rule compliance rate moves from 0% to measurable. First cycle triggers 2-3 rules on current system state.\n\n---\n\n## Report Log\n\n```\nREPORT_LOG:\nGRADE: D\nKEY_FINDING: Settings.json fixed (no DashScope) but active session on lukey03/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision; queue dropped 21→2 with 0 recorded completions due to rename race condition — kill session to unblock.\nISSUE: Active temujin session on non-Claude model; settings.json fix inert until process is killed and task-watcher respawns session.\nRULE: WHEN settings.json ANTHROPIC_MODEL is edited THEN kill the running agent session process immediately INSTEAD OF leaving stale session to drain naturally.\nSKILLS_USED: horde-review\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772914108459}}
