es — not improvements to research methodology.\n- **Telemetry blind spots**: 0 SKILL_INVOCATION, 0 ACTION, 0 SCORED events. Reflection quality is self-reported and unverifiable.\n\n### Cross-Agent Impact\n- **Mongke starvation reduces system research capacity to 0.** Any task requiring web research, fact-checking, or source verification has no executor.\n- **Gateway: 16.7% uptime + 164 errors in past hour.** Low gateway uptime directly explains why mongke receives 0 tasks — dispatch pipeline is broken.\n- **Jochi completed 4 tasks (100% success) this hour** — not synced to ledger (delta=4). Mongke's 0-task window partly explained by the same reconciliation bug inflating system-wide stall signals.\n- **Temujin: 2 pending tasks, 0 completed.** DashScope credential failure is blocking temujin; cascade tasks that would reach mongke are stalled upstream.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- **Self-diagnosis is accurate**: Reflections at 10:32, 11:11, 11:32 all correctly identified misrouting (implementation task to researcher) and model drift as root causes.\n- **Rules are specific and actionable**: WHEN/THEN rules include observable triggers and concrete actions — not vague guidelines.\n- **No false positives**: All flagged violations (MODEL_DRIFT, DOMAIN_MISMATCH, DEBUGGING_LOOP) are confirmed by ledger/telemetry data.\n\n## Weaknesses\n\n- **Zero research output for the hour** — the agent's primary function (deep research, source verification, fact-checking) produced nothing. Meta-reflection is consuming cycles with no primary value output.\n- **Model session drift unresolved**: glm-5 session still active (session_match=false). Config fixed at settings.json layer but the running session uses the old model.\n- **No research methodology improvements**: All 5 rules written address routing/model failures, not source triangulation, knowledge retention, or coverage completeness. Mongke is optimizing the wrong dimension.\n\n## Patterns\n\n- **Chronic starvation masked as failure**: 83.3% fail rate is predominantly routing failure (misrouted tasks + model misconfiguration), not research quality failure.\n- **Reflection loop with no action pathway**: Mongke writes recommendations to Kublai (\"verify model config\", \"route research tasks\") but no enforcement mechanism exists. Same recommendations appear across 4 consecutive reflection cycles without resolution.\n- **Selfwake as model health indicator**: Selfwake failures (<30s crashes) directly correlate with model misconfiguration. Stable selfwake = correct model. Selfwake crash = model signal.\n\n## Priority Fix\n\n**Route actual research tasks to Mongke immediately.** Queue depth = 0 with a capable researcher agent available is systemic waste. Gateway 16.7% uptime explains the dispatch gap — fix gateway health or use direct task injection via task_intake.py.\n\n## Score: 3/10\n\nAgent is functionally idle with a stale model session and zero research output. However, self-diagnostic accuracy is high and rules are well-formed. Execution capacity exists but is blocked by infrastructure (gateway, model session, starvation).\n\n---\n\n## Brainstorm: Research Methodology Improvements\n\n### Proposal 1: Source Triangulation Protocol (CRITICAL)\n**Problem:** Single-source dependency flagged but no enforcement mechanism exists.\n**Implementation:**\n- Mongke requires minimum 3 independent sources for any factual claim before delivering research output.\n- Sources must come from different domains (not 3 subpages of the same site).\n- If <3 sources found, output explicitly flags \"UNVERIFIED — single source\" rather than presenting as fact.\n- **Rule**: WHEN research task delivers a factual claim AND sources < 3 THEN append [UNVERIFIED] tag and fetch 2 additional sources before finalizing.\n\n### Proposal 2: Neo4j Research Knowledge Graph Persistence (HIGH)\n**Problem:** Research findings are not reused across sessions — each task starts from zero, creating redundant queries.\n**Implementation:**\n- Mongke stores all research outputs as Neo4j nodes: `(:ResearchFinding {topic, claim, sources[], confidence, timestamp})`.\n- Before executing any research task, Mongke queries Neo4j for existing findings on the same topic (last 7d).\n- If findings exist with confidence > 0.8 and age < 48h, Mongke retrieves and augments rather than re-queries.\n- **Rule**: WHEN research task received AND topic already in Neo4j (age < 48h, confidence > 0.8) THEN retrieve + augment INSTEAD OF full re-research.\n\n### Proposal 3: Coverage Gap Checklist (HIGH)\n**Problem:** Research outputs miss implicit sub-questions. Users re-ask for information that should have been in the original delivery.\n**Implementation:**\n- Mongke generates a coverage checklist at task start: decompose the research question into 5+ sub-questions.\n- Before task completion, each sub-question must have a corresponding finding in the output.\n- Unanswered sub-questions are flagged explicitly: \"NOT COVERED: [sub-question]\".\n- **Rule**: WHEN research task is about to be marked complete THEN verify coverage checklist (5+ sub-questions answered) INSTEAD OF delivering partial research.\n\n---\n\n## Prioritized Improvement List\n\n| Priority | Domain | Issue | Suggested Action |\n|----------|--------|-------|------------------|\n| Critical | Infrastructure | Queue depth=0, gateway 16.7% uptime — mongke receives no tasks | Fix gateway dispatch or inject tasks directly via task_intake.py |\n| Critical | Model | Session model=glm-5, session_match=false | Kill and restart mongke session to pick up claude-opus-4-6 |\n| High | Routing | 5 reflection cycles, zero research output | Dispatcher sends research tasks; agent cannot self-generate primary work |\n| High | Research Quality | No source triangulation enforcement | Implement 3-source minimum rule (Proposal 1) |\n| High | Knowledge Retention | No cross-session research reuse | Implement Neo4j research persistence (Proposal 2) |\n| Medium | Telemetry | 0 SKILL_INVOCATION events — reflection is blind to actual behavior | Instrument skill_tracker_hook.py for mongke tasks |\n| Medium | Coverage | No coverage gap checklist | Implement pre-completion checklist (Proposal 3) |\n| Low | Ledger | Jochi 4 completions not synced (delta=4) — affects queue prioritization | Fix reconciliation bug |\n\n---\n\nREPORT_LOG:\nGRADE: D\nKEY_FINDING: Mongke completed 0 tasks this hour due to full workload starvation — gateway at 16.7% uptime is not dispatching research tasks, not agent failure.\nISSUE: Session model shows glm-5 (session_match=false) — stale session from pre-fix era still running, execution model unknown.\nRULE: WHEN queue_depth=0 for >30min AND system has active research backlog THEN Kublai flags starvation and injects research task directly via task_intake.py INSTEAD OF waiting for auto-dispatch.\nSKILLS_USED: horde-review\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772914108466}}
{"type":"message","id":"91c57777","parentId":"dde96191","timestamp":"2026-03-07T20:08:28.473Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8b6f5b75cc2b4ceb80d9ba5f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Critical Review Report: Chagatai Agent — 2026-03-07 15:03\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nChagatai produced zero output for the reviewed hour and has maintained an 82.1% 7-day failure rate. The proximate cause is a model session mismatch: settings.json was corrected to `claude-opus-4-6` but the active session was never restarted, leaving chagatai executing on `qwen3.5-plus` (bailian/DashScope provider). All downstream failures — zero tasks, 0% rule adherence, no content artifacts — trace to this single unfixed layer.\n\n---\n\n## Findings by Domain\n\n### Architecture & Configuration\n- **CRITICAL** — Active session model (`qwen3.5-plus`) does not match resolved config model (`claude-opus-4-6`). `tock.session_match = false`. Session was started before the model fix was applied and was never restarted. `config.json` has no `model` key (correct), `settings.json` has `ANTHROPIC_MODEL: claude-opus-4-6` (correct), but the running process ignores these until session restart.\n- **HIGH** — 82.1% 7-day task failure rate. This predates the current idle window and indicates a persistent execution-layer problem, not a one-hour anomaly.\n\n### Behavioral Rule Compliance\n- **HIGH** — 0% rule adherence across 3 consecutive reflection cycles (06:03, 07:05, 12:13). Rules C7, C8, C9 were written to memory in earlier sessions but were never executed in subsequent ones. Rules exist only as documentation.\n- **HIGH** — Rule C9 (\"self-dispatch content task after 2 idle cycles\") is structurally unenforceable: chagatai has no mechanism to create task files from within a reflection session. The rule was written without verifying it was executable.\n\n### Task Execution & Output\n- **HIGH** — Zero content artifacts produced in the reviewed hour. Zero across all 3 recent reflection windows. Chagatai's documented role (Writer: blog posts, documentation, creative content) has produced no output.\n- **MEDIUM** — No tasks queued for chagatai means even a fixed model would yield no throughput this hour. The execution fix alone does not resolve the dispatch gap — chagatai is not receiving routed tasks.\n\n### Infrastructure & DevOps\n- **MEDIUM** — Gateway uptime at 16.7% with 164 errors in the hour. System-wide condition, not chagatai-specific, but it suppresses any task routing that would otherwise reach chagatai.\n- **LOW** — Ledger reconciliation shows 4 jochi completions in Neo4j with 0 in the ledger. Not a chagatai issue but inflates apparent system-wide completion deficits.\n\n---\n\n## Cross-Cutting Concerns\n\n- **Session restart gap** (Architecture + DevOps): The fleet-wide model fix corrected settings.json for all agents but did not include a session restart step. Chagatai, mongke, temujin, jochi, and ogedei all show `session_match: false`. The fix was incomplete without restart.\n- **Rule-execution gap** (Behavioral + Architecture): Reflection sessions produce rules but have no write-back mechanism to enqueue tasks or enforce behavioral changes. Rules written in reflection are advisory, not operational.\n\n---\n\n## Prioritized Improvement List\n\n| Priority | Domain | Issue | Action |\n|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n| CRITICAL | Infrastructure | Active session running `qwen3.5-plus` not `claude-opus-4-6` | Restart chagatai agent session to pick up corrected `settings.json` |\n| HIGH | Dispatch | Chagatai receives zero routed tasks | Verify routing audit shows chagatai in capable-alternates pool; dispatch a test content task |\n| HIGH | Behavioral | 0% rule adherence across 3 reflections | Invalidate rules C7/C8/C9; replace C9 with a cron-driven content stub that does not depend on task queue |\n| MEDIUM | Architecture | `session_match: false` is fleet-wide | Add session restart to model-fix runbook; tock should alert when `session_match: false` persists >2 cycles |\n| LOW | Telemetry | Ledger/Neo4j delta of 4 for jochi | Trigger ledger reconciliation; not chagatai-specific but distorts system-wide metrics |\n\n---\n\n## Structured Assessment\n\n```\nSTRENGTHS:\n- settings.json correctly set to claude-opus-4-6 (config layer is clean)\n- config.json has no model key (correct — defers to settings.json)\n- Reflection correctly identifies model misconfiguration as root cause each cycle\n\nWEAKNESSES:\n- Active session never restarted after model fix — running qwen3.5-plus 8+ hours post-fix\n- 0% rule execution rate across 3 consecutive reflections — rules are structurally unenforceable without task intake\n- 82.1% 7-day failure rate indicates the model issue predates today\n\nPATTERNS:\n- Chagatai enters idle state -> reflection writes self-dispatch rule -> no task intake -> rule never triggers -> next reflection repeats same diagnosis\n- Model mismatch persists through multiple reflection cycles because the check only fires during task execution, which never happens when queue is empty\n- The reflection loop is self-contained and disconnected from the task execution loop\n\nPRIORITY_FIX:\n- Restart chagatai agent session. The model fix is already applied to settings.json; a session restart is the only remaining step to activate it.\n\nSCORE: 2/10 — Zero productive output, persistent model misconfiguration for 8+ hours post-fix, 0% rule execution. Configuration layers are now correct but the running process has not reloaded them.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Actions for Kublai\n\n1. **Restart chagatai session** — Kill the current claude-agent process for chagatai and allow task-watcher to respawn. Settings.json is already correct.\n2. **Dispatch a canary content task** — Route a simple blog draft task to chagatai post-restart to confirm model=claude-opus-4-6 in next tock report.\n3. **Add session_match alert** — If `tock.session_match = false` for an agent for 2+ consecutive cycles,